  "title": "How to create Mount script for azure fileshare",
  "slug": "how-to-create-mount-script-for-azure-fileshare",
  "categorySlug": "data-sources",
  "html": "<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid\">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-cell \" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"cell\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n\n<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper row-depth-1 row-number-1 dnd-section kb-article-row-0-padding\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid \">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-cell dnd-column\" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"cell\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n\n<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper row-depth-1 row-number-2 dnd-row\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid \">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-custom_widget dnd-module\" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"custom_widget\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-2\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\">\n\n</div>\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div><!--end row-->\n</div><!--end row-wrapper -->\n\n<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper row-depth-1 row-number-3 dnd-row\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid \">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-custom_widget dnd-module\" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"custom_widget\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-3\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\">\n  <h1 id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-3_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_inline_text_field\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"inline_text_field\">How to create&nbsp;Mount script for azure fileshare</h1>\n</div>\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div><!--end row-->\n</div><!--end row-wrapper -->\n\n<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper row-depth-1 row-number-4 dnd-row\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid \">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-custom_widget dnd-module\" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"custom_widget\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-4\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\">\n  <h2 id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-4_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_inline_text_field\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"inline_text_field\">Here is a script of the actions taken within the Microsoft Azure Portal, followed by key notes summarizing the process.</h2>\n</div>\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div><!--end row-->\n</div><!--end row-wrapper -->\n\n<div class=\"row-fluid-wrapper row-depth-1 row-number-5 dnd-row\">\n<div class=\"row-fluid \">\n<div class=\"span12 widget-span widget-type-custom_widget dnd-module\" style=\"\" data-widget-type=\"custom_widget\" data-x=\"0\" data-w=\"12\">\n<div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-5\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_module\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"module\">\n  <div id=\"hs_cos_wrapper_kb-article-module-5_\" class=\"hs_cos_wrapper hs_cos_wrapper_widget hs_cos_wrapper_type_inline_richtext_field\" style=\"\" data-hs-cos-general-type=\"widget\" data-hs-cos-type=\"inline_richtext_field\"><h3><strong>Visual steps</strong></h3>\n<ol>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">The video begins on the Azure Portal Home.&nbsp;\n<ol>\n<li aria-level=\"2\">The user navigates to the <strong>Storage accounts</strong> service.</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">From the list of available storage accounts, the user selects the account named fx. <strong>storage304</strong>.</li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">The Overview blade for storage304 loads.&nbsp;\n<ol>\n<li aria-level=\"2\">The user navigates to the left-hand menu.</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Under the \"Data storage\" section in the left menu,&nbsp;\n<ol>\n<li aria-level=\"2\">The user clicks on <strong>File shares</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">The list of file shares loads.&nbsp;\n<ol>\n<li aria-level=\"2\">The user clicks on the share named <strong>fileshare</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">The overview page for the specific file share opens.&nbsp;\n<ol>\n<li aria-level=\"2\">The user moves the cursor to the top toolbar and clicks the <strong>Connect</strong> button.</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">A \"Connect\" pane slides out from the right side of the screen. By default, the \"Windows\" tab is selected.\n<ol>\n<li aria-level=\"2\">The user clicks on the <strong>Linux</strong> tab.</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Under the Linux settings,&nbsp;\n<ol>\n<li aria-level=\"2\">The user clicks the button labeled <strong>Show script</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">The video ends as the pre-generated mount script is revealed.</li>\n</ol>\n<hr><div class=\"hs-video-widget\" data-hsv-embed-id=\"e63cc74b-38ac-40a5-97b8-87e4c33e3f92\">\n  <div class=\"hs-video-container\" style=\"max-width: 1464px; margin: 0 auto;\">\n    <div class=\"hs-video-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; height: 0; padding-bottom: 63.52%\">\n      <iframe data-hsv-src=\"https://play.hubspotvideo.com/v/4381120/id/205118511511\" referrerpolicy=\"origin\" sandbox=\"allow-forms allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen;\" style=\"position: absolute !important; width: 100% !important; height: 100% !important; left: 0; top: 0; border: 0 none; pointer-events: initial\" title=\"HubSpot Video\" loading=\"lazy\" data-hsv-id=\"205118511511\" data-hsv-style=\"\" data-hsv-width=\"1464\" data-hsv-height=\"930\" data-hsv-autoplay=\"false\" data-hsv-loop=\"false\" data-hsv-muted=\"false\" data-hsv-hidden-controls=\"false\" data-hsv-full-width=\"false\"></iframe>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<h3><strong>Generating a Mount Script</strong></h3>\n<p>The standard procedure for obtaining the code necessary to mount an Azure File Share to a local machine or a Virtual Machine (VM).</p>\n<h4><strong>1. Navigation Path</strong></h4>\n<p>To replicate this process, follow this hierarchy:</p>\n<p><strong>Home</strong> $\\rightarrow$ <strong>Storage Accounts</strong> $\\rightarrow$ <strong>[Your Storage Account]</strong> $\\rightarrow$ <strong>File Shares</strong> $\\rightarrow$ <strong>[Your Share Name]</strong></p>\n<h4><strong>2. The \"Connect\" Feature</strong></h4>\n<p>The <strong>Connect</strong> button is the shortcut to generating connection strings and mount scripts. It automatically handles the syntax for authentication, including the storage account name and the access key.</p>\n<h4><strong>3. OS Compatibility</strong></h4>\n<p>Note that Azure provides unique scripts for different operating systems. You can see tabs for:</p>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\"1\"><strong>Windows:</strong> Uses PowerShell.</li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\"><strong>Linux:</strong> Uses the SMB protocol via the terminal (the option selected in the video).</li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\"><strong>macOS:</strong> Uses the standard mount command.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>4. The Generated Script</strong></h4>\n<p>The script generated includes:</p>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Creation of a local directory (mount point).</li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">Storage account credentials (username and password/key).</li>\n<li aria-level=\"1\">The mount command specifying the SMB version (usually 3.0) and the server path.</li>\n</ul>\n<ol>\n<li><strong> Send the script to </strong><a href=\"mailto:support@dataandmore.com\"><strong>support@dataandmore.com</strong></a></li>\n</ol>\n<br>\n<p>Please send the LINUX generated script to Data &amp; More.</p></div>\n</div>\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div><!--end row-->\n</div><!--end row-wrapper -->\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div><!--end row-->\n</div><!--end row-wrapper -->\n\n</div><!--end widget-span -->\n</div>\n</div>",
  "sourceUrl": "https://support.dataandmore.com/en/knowledge/how-to-create-mount-script-for-azure-fileshare"
